        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed on three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells) using the Richardson extrapolation procedure per Celik et al. (2008). GCI on relative hemolysis index < 5% required; achieved GCI = 2.3%. Gradation 3 achieved."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted with refinement ratio r = 1.4. GCI on the primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) was computed as 2.3%, well below the 5% acceptance threshold. The medium mesh (5.8M cells) was selected for production runs, providing an adequate balance between accuracy and computational cost."
