      "rationale": "The Test Samples factor addresses variability arising from physical specimen-to-specimen differences in experimental test articles. This factor is not applicable to the present COU because validation is performed against the FDA generic centrifugal pump, a single reference geometry with no manufactured specimen variability. All experimental data were collected on a single precision-machined reference pump; no population of test samples exists, and specimen-to-specimen variability is therefore outside the scope of this credibility assessment."
